Hyde Park is a TypeScript monorepo for independently versioned npm packages.

Codex Note:

- If this file was reached from `AGENTS.md`, treat it as the default repository context for nearly all Hyde Park tasks.
- Use it to identify the canonical docs to read next, not as a replacement for the detailed documentation in `docs/`.

Core repository facts:

- Public leaf packages are the primary product.
- `@ddosdor/hyde-park` is a convenience umbrella package.
- Public package categories currently include `composables`, `utils`, `fun`, and `meta`.
- Private workspace packages include `packages/tooling/*` and `apps/docs`.
- The repository uses `pnpm`, `Turborepo`, `tsup`, `Changesets`, `Vitest`, `ESLint`, and `VitePress`.

Canonical maintainer docs live in:

- `@docs/project-overview.md`
- `@docs/workspace-structure.md`
- `@docs/tooling-guide.md`
- `@docs/package-standards.md`
- `@docs/creating-packages.md`
- `@docs/release-guide.md`
- `@docs/commands-reference.md`
- `@docs/troubleshooting.md`

When working in this repo:

- Prefer the existing workspace conventions over inventing new structure.
- Keep public packages independently installable and independently versioned.
- Keep private tooling and docs packages private.
- Keep AI-facing context in `AGENTS.md` and `.cursor/` aligned with the actual repository implementation.
